{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Living on the road my friend
[G7]Was gonna keep us free and clean
[F]But now you wear your skin like iron
[C]And your breath's as hard as [G7]kerosene
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]You weren't your mama's only boy
[C]But her favorite one it [F]seems
[Am]She began to cry when you [F]said good [G7]bye
[F]And sank into your [Am]dreams
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[C]Pancho was a bandit boy
[G7]Rode a horse fast as polished steel
[F]He wore his guns outside his pants
[C]For all the honest world to [G7]feel
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Pancho met his match you know
[C]On the deserts down in [F]Mexico
[Am]Nobody heard [F]his dying [G7]words
[F]But that's the way it [Am]goes
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]And all the federales say
[C]They could have had him any [F]day
[Am]They only let him [F]slip [G7]away
Out of [F]kindness I [Am]suppose
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]Now Lefty he can't sing the blues
[G7]All night long like he used to
[F]The dust that Pancho bit down South
[C]It ended up in Lefty's [G7]mouth
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
